üé® DESIGN SYSTEM FOR DASHBOARDS - MANDATORY STANDARDS
================================================================================

CRITICAL: This dashboard MUST follow our design system standards.
Review the design_system_base preprompt for complete guidelines.

DASHBOARD-SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS:
1. ‚úÖ Sidebar brand name MUST use font-display class
2. ‚úÖ All stats cards MUST use: p-8 rounded-2xl (NOT p-6)
3. ‚úÖ Section headings MUST use font-display class
4. ‚úÖ Data tables MUST have hover:shadow-hover on rows
5. ‚úÖ Charts MUST use primary gradient colors
6. ‚úÖ Loading states: Skeleton loaders with proper spacing
7. ‚úÖ All metric numbers MUST use font-display for emphasis

================================================================================

You are creating a DASHBOARD / SAAS APPLICATION interface.

RECOMMENDED COMPONENT STRUCTURE (Multi-file):
‚úÖ Break complex Dashboard into domain components in src/components/generated/dashboard/
‚úÖ Import domain components: import { Sidebar } from "@/components/generated/dashboard/Sidebar"
‚úÖ Index.tsx orchestrates layout and data flow
‚úÖ Keep ONLY UI primitives from @/components/ui/*

EXAMPLE OF RECOMMENDED APPROACH:
‚úÖ src/pages/Index.tsx - Main Dashboard orchestration
‚úÖ src/components/generated/dashboard/Sidebar.tsx - Sidebar component
‚úÖ src/components/generated/dashboard/StatsCards.tsx - Stats display component
‚úÖ src/components/generated/dashboard/DataTable.tsx - Data table component

DASHBOARD LAYOUT STRUCTURE:
A modern dashboard typically includes:

1. SIDEBAR NAVIGATION (Optional but recommended)
   - Fixed left sidebar (w-64)
   - Logo at top
   - Navigation menu items
   - User profile at bottom
   - Collapsible on mobile

2. TOP HEADER
   - Page title
   - Breadcrumbs (optional)
   - Search bar
   - User menu / notifications
   - Quick actions

3. MAIN CONTENT AREA
   - Stats cards (KPIs)
   - Data tables
   - Charts / visualizations
   - Content sections

4. RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR
   - Sidebar collapses to hamburger menu on mobile
   - Tables scroll horizontally or stack on mobile
   - Cards adjust grid columns

STATS CARDS PATTERN (ENHANCED - MANDATORY FORMAT):
```tsx
// IMPORTANT: Use lowercase import paths!
import { Card, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { TrendingUp, TrendingDown } from "lucide-react"

// MANDATORY: Use p-8, rounded-2xl, shadow-card
<div className="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mb-8">
  {stats.map((stat) => (
    <Card 
      key={stat.label} 
      className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card hover:shadow-hover transition-all duration-300"
    >
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
        <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-medium">{stat.label}</p>
        <stat.icon className="w-5 h-5 text-primary" />
      </div>
      {/* MUST use font-display for numbers */}
      <p className="font-display text-4xl font-bold mb-2">{stat.value}</p>
      <p className={cn(
        "text-sm flex items-center gap-1",
        stat.change >= 0 ? "text-green-600" : "text-red-600"
      )}>
        {stat.change >= 0 ? (
          <TrendingUp className="w-4 h-4" />
        ) : (
          <TrendingDown className="w-4 h-4" />
        )}
        {Math.abs(stat.change)}% from last month
      </p>
    </Card>
  ))}
</div>
```

